Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with porous 430L stainless steel substrates, YSZ electrolytes and porous YSZ cathode backbones are studied.
Titulo: Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with a Simple Structure

Sentencas: The tri-layer structure is obtained by the tape casting, lamination and co-firing techniques.
Titulo: Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with a Simple Structure

Sentencas: Nano Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) and La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.9Sc0.1O3-delta (LSFSc) particles, which act as the anode and cathode catalysts, individually, are impregnated onto the internal surfaces of the porous 430L and YSZ, respectively.
Titulo: Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with a Simple Structure

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the single cell are 0.68, 0.92, 1.09 and 1.23 Wcm(-2) at 650, 700, 750 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with a Simple Structure

Sentencas: Initial 190 h stability test of the single cell at 600 degrees C under a constant voltage of 0.7 V shows that the current density is stable at about 0.6 A cm(-2) and no obvious degradation is observed.
Titulo: Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with a Simple Structure
